Create a template file with variables using the similar shell syntax:
$ vi tmp.tmpl my_config_key_1=&amp;quot;${MY_CONFIG_KEY_1}&amp;quot; my_config_key_2=&amp;quot;${MY_CONFIG_KEY_2}&amp;quot; Render the template with envsubst:
$ export MY_CONFIG_KEY_1=tony MY_CONFIG_KEY_2=cesaro $ envsubst &amp;lt; tmp.tmpl my_config_key_1=&amp;quot;tony&amp;quot; my_config_key_2=&amp;quot;cesaro&amp;quot; 2021-05-29 # [vim] Convert line indention from 2 to 4 spaces
